						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/S-T-Policy/ICKM-MIS-ICT/Related-developments/A-systems-approach-to-understand-biodiversity" title="A systems approach to understand biodiversity" alt="link">A systems approach to understand biodiversity</a></h2>

	
					<p>Central to the approach is a need to standardise, store openly, and link together disparate datasets in a fully interoperable way. The field of genomics serves as a useful analogy, with a culture of openness in data sharing, standardisation and tool development.<a href="http://blogs.biomedcentral.com/bmcseriesblog/2013/04/15/a-systems-approach-to-understand-biodiversity/" target="_self">http://blogs.biomedcentral.com/bmcseriesblog/2013/04/15/a-systems-approach-to-understand-biodiversity/</a>(BioMed Central, 15/04/2013)</p>
